C

client - package client
The client package contains all the java classes responsible for client logic, GUI and event handling.
ClientController - Class in client
ClientController class handles the Listeners for the clientview.
ClientController() - Constructor for class client.ClientController
Class constructor that adds listeners to the components in the Clientview.
ClientHandler - Class in server
Contains the logic for communicating with the client over the objectinputstream and objectoutputstream.
ClientHandler(Socket) - Constructor for class server.ClientHandler
class constructor opens an objectStream to be used
ClientModel - Class in client
Contains the logic for communicating with the server over the objectinputstream and objectoutputstream.
ClientModel() - Constructor for class client.ClientModel
Class constructor that creates the socket that communicates with the server and initializes the objectoutputstream and objectinputstream from that socket.
ClientView - Class in client
The ClientView displays the information that the client gets from the server in the chat window.
ClientView() - Constructor for class client.ClientView
Class constructor that provides the ClientView with a clientModel so that it can display data and fetch data from the clientModel.
closeConnection() - Method in class client.ClientModel
Closes the client connection in case of an error.
closeConnection() - Method in class server.ClientHandler
closes server connection incase of an error or user disconnects close all sockets and streams to free resources
connectToServer() - Method in class client.ClientModel
re-initializes the socket and object streams when the connect button is pressed in case the server was not running when the client started
